        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 5:49PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles east of Colville, or 41 miles northwest of Priest River, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Little Pend Oreille Lakes Campground.

This includes U.S. Highway 20 in Washington between mile markers 372
and 381.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
